post_text:
Congratulations to our Northwest Staff of the Week!!

Susie Crabb has transferred to a self contained room this year after spending years in the preschool room. She has done a wonderful job with the transfer. The students have really taken to her as she shows them love and compassion.

Veronica Jenkins is one of our speech teachers who has helped our students thrive. Veronica this year is trying a new adventure and is working at the junior high school and at NW. Even though many of her students are online she still finds ways to connect with them and for them to find success.

Courtney Klobucher is one of our fifth grade teachers who is a part of our PBIS team. She is always brainstorming and coming up with ideas to help improve our school. She is a leader in the school even though this is only her second year in the district.

post_text:
Congratulations to our Northwest staff Of the week!

Holli is a kind person who is always willing to give her time and energy for her students and her coworkers. Besides leaving goodies in the lounge for staff, she has also donated jump ropes for our PE class. She is compassionate and caring to all that pass her through her classroom.

Sandy is a veteran teacher who is braving a new frontier, online teaching. She is going forward to this new adventure with a positive attitude. She will bless all her students in-person and online with her wealth of knowledge. She has high standards for her students that allow for future success.

Wendy is a second year paraprofessional in preK. She is always willing to help in the classroom and in the rest of the building. She is a perfect match working with our littles by always demonstrating kindness and patience. She is an asset to our Northwest family.

Tuesday, August 25th all students coming to school face to face need breakfast prior to our first student-day (8/26). They can pick up their 8/26 grab-and-go breakfast at LJH from 12:30-2:00 (one breakfast per student) on Linberg Ave at the cafeteria drive up. After we start, when half-day students are present in class daily, their bag-breakfast and bag-lunch will be given to them at dismissal to take home.

Online-only-student meal pick up will be Wednesdays starting Aug. 26th from 12:30-2 on Linberg Ave at the LJH cafeteria drive up. We will disperse student's breakfast and lunch meal boxes (equivalent to 5 breakfast meals & 5 lunch meals) weekly on Wednesdays from 12:30-2.

Lincoln Junior High Baseball has 2 away games this week. Tuesday at Peru Parkside (bus @ 3:45) & Thursday @ Ottawa Shepherd (bus @ 3:30). Anyone who wants to drive separately is more than welcome to, just contact Coach Urbanski or Mr. Blumhorst.

If you are going to ride the bus, you will have your temperature checked and have to complete a quick questionnaire before getting on the bus. MASKS ARE REQUIRED ON THE BUS!

Coach Urbanski has uniforms and hats, just remember to get your grey baseball pants.

If you have any questions, please email Mr. Blumhorst - blumhorstc@lasalleschools.net

LAST DAY AND WE HAVE A LOT OF FOOD TO GIVE AWAY!!!

REMINDER: Today, Thursday, July 30th is summer meal pick-up! Come to Lincoln Junior High anytime between 9am-12pm to grab your meals!

‚Ä¢ Meals will be provided to LaSalle residents who are age 18 and under for the summer months. Meals are not restricted to LaSalle Elementary Students as L-P students or other children meeting the above requirement are eligible for meal service.

‚Ä¢ Meals will be distributed as curbside self-service at Lincoln Junior High only. Meals will be set along the bus lane (Lindberg Ave) at Lincoln Junior High, and families will be required to load vehicles themselves.

‚Ä¢ Meals will be distributed in bulk meal packages, breakfast & lunch combined, with the intent to provide meal service for the entire week.

post_text:
Northwest Parents/Guardians,

Come join us for a short training on how your student will be accessing Remote Learning Platforms through their District assigned Google Account and Chromebook.
This short in-person training with your NW students will be offered on August 10th and August 11th at Northwest Elementary School.
You can sign up for a 30 min time slot by clicking here
https://calendly.com/mclendonk/nw-guardian-student-remote-technology-training?month=2020-08

There will be a max of 10 other parents/guardians with their students per time slot.
The following topics will be covered: connecting to a wireless network, signing into the student's Google Account and Chromebook, previewing the Chrome Browser, Bookmark Bar, and Google Classroom.

These training sessions will be presented by our District's Technology Coordinator, Mrs. Kirsten McLendon.

Who is ready to read a good book?

LaSalle Elementary is starting a Lynx Book Club for 3rd grade - Jr. High students. Students will be able to join, check out selected books every two weeks to read and be able to participate in virtual book club discussions. Mrs. Tipton and Miss Rapp will be posting activities available in the Lynx Book Club Google Classroom. Books may be picked up at Northwest or be delivered to your home. Contact tiptonl@lasalleschools.net or text 815-993-2695 for more information and join. Book selection starts Friday June 19th.

PSA for all soon-to-be kindergarten parents...
Practice eating ‚Äúschool lunch‚Äù with your kiddo. Make sure they can open everything you send with them. Talk about not eating off of the table in the lunchroom!!! Set a timer for 20 minutes and talk about how they may not finish eating and that‚Äôs ok. Practice packing everything back up and talk about what is trash and what should come back home in their lunch box. Kindergarten lunch is a big adjustment and your child‚Äôs teacher will be super appreciative if you have prepared them for the experience!

post_text:
Feed His Children is having a "Drive-Thru Donation Day" on Saturday, April 25 from 10-2.
The list of items we're asking for is in the photo below, as well as a traffic flow map of the Crossbridge Peru campus. If you'd be so kind as to share with family and friends, and post to the school's social media if you're able, we'd appreciate it.
Grocery stores are just starting to allow us to order again, so the more that we get, the more we'll be able to bless the families we serve. We do ask that people purchase no more than three of each item to be respectful of everyone!
People donating will just drive up, open their trunks, and a volunteer will take the food out of their trunk, so there's no contact at all.

post_text: Late Friday, Governor Pritkzer ordered all Illinois public schools to suspend student attendance starting Tuesday, March 17, 2020 through at least March 30, 2020. The suspension of student attendance is a precautionary step in addressing the spread of COVID-19 (coronavirus). LES #122 will be in attendance on Monday, March 16, 2020 for full services, but will implement a 2:00 dismissal for students. Moving forward, students are not to report to school until at least March 31, 2020. Parents/Guardians: Please be prepared for students to bring home the necessary materials and supplies from the school at the conclusion of Monday. The district will update when further information is known.

Congratulations to our Northwest Staff of the Week!
Jamie Walker, Mrs. Walker is amazing in the classroom. She greets every child with a smile in the morning and her students are eager to start their day. Mrs. Walker takes care of the Rocky cart and finds volunteers and replenishes the cart with goodies so all students can earn valuable rewards for good behavior. Mrs. Walker is also a vital part of the PBIS tier 1 team who find ways to celebrate our students throughout the year.
Jessica Weber, Mrs. Weber has the patience like a saint. In the most difficult situations, she stays calm and collective. She treats her students with respect and love which creates a warm environment which is inviting for all who enter her room. All students know they are appreciated for their differences in Mrs. Weber's room.

Julie Crowther, Julie is a reading interventionist. Besides improving our students' reading skills and making our students feel special, she is a team player who many times subs for other teachers in the building at a moments notice without complaint. She is a leader in our building for our Aimsweb Plus program. She gives great insight for our curriculum committee in the search for our new instructional program in ELA.
Melissa Silfies, Missy is an amazing paraprofessional who stays long after everyone leaves to ride our bus to help our students. She is patient and kind to our students who need a little extra help. She is constantly looking for ways to help her students and to learn new strategies. Missy is always positive and flexible with her schedule to help out our students or our school.
